# Sky culture name
msgid "Egyptian"
msgstr "Egyptian"

# Sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"Late Egyptian astronomy/astrology follows that of Greco/Roman culture. The "
"belief that the stars could influence human destiny does not appear to have "
"reached Egypt until the Ptolemaic period. The temple of Hathor at Denderah "
"dates from Ptolemaic times, probably the first century BCE, and has a "
"wonderful illustration of the sky that illustrates this point."
msgstr ""
"De moderne Egyptische astronomie/astrologie volgt die van de Grieks/Romeinse "
"cultuur. Het geloof dat de sterren het menselijk lot kunnen beïnvloeden "
"schijnt Egypte niet hebben bereikt tot de Ptolemaeusse periode. De tempel "
"van Hathor in Denderah dateert uit de Ptolemaeusse tijd, ongeveer de eerste "
"eeuw v.Chr, en heeft een prachtige illustratie van de hemel dat dit punt "
"illustreert."

# Sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"However there were differences in names. For example, Cancer the Crab is "
"represented by the Scarab Beetle. The figure of the Lion near the Scales "
"(which is not the zodiacal Lion) is the constellation Centaurus [#1].\n"
"\n"
"Earlier constellations are more problematic, but some indications exist that "
"some modern zodiac signs are very ancient indeed [#2], although the "
"constellations did change significantly over time [#3].\n"
"\n"
"The Egyptians recognized five planets and called them the \"stars that knew "
"no rest\". Their movement across the heavens reminded the Egyptians of the "
"five gods sailing across the sky in their solar barque (boat). The planet "
"now known as Jupiter was called \"Horus Who Limits the Two Lands\"; Mars was "
"\"Horus of the Horizon\"; Mercury was \"Sebegu\", associated with Set; "
"Saturn was \"Horus the Bull of the Sky\"; and Venus was \"the God of the "
"Morning\" [#7]."
msgstr ""
"Niettemin zijn er verschillen in namen. Bijvoorbeeld, de Kreeft wordt "
"vertegenwoordigd door de Mestkever. De figuur van de Leeuw in de buurt van "
"de Weegschaal (dat is niet de dierenriem Leeuw) is het sterrenbeeld "
"Centaurus [1].\n"
"\n"
"Vroegere sterrenbeelden zijn problematischer, maar er bestaan aanwijzingen "
"dat sommige moderne dierenriemtekens inderdaad zeer oud zijn [2], hoewel de "
"sterrenbeelden niet significant veranderen in de tijd [3].\n"
"\n"
"De Egyptenaren kenden vijf planeten en noemden ze \"rusteloze sterren\". Hun "
"beweging aan de hemel herinnerde de Egyptenaren aan de vijf goden die in hun "
"zonnebark (boot) over de hemel zeilden. De planeet die we nu kennen als "
"Jupiter werd genoemd \"Horus die de Twee Landen Verenigt\"; Mars was \"Horus "
"van de Horizon\"; Mercurius was \"Sebegu\", geassocieerd met ondergang; "
"Saturnus was \"Horus de Stier van de Hemel\"; Venus was \"God van de Ochtend"
"\" [7]."

